author: @WDDYPP
text:
I think those people who are just gonna take everything so literally and hate on people just doing their job & creating music for the rest of us, gotta stop listening to at least 90% of the music out there. Almost every title and every song content could be a trauma?! If the song has gunshots= trigger. Dynamite/explosion = trigger. Sex-related = trigger. At this point, even if the song talks about eating meat, are the vegans gonna bash it?! Geez. 
Also the live incident has nothing to do with the actual music? 20 boys talking over each other on live, it was already chaotic. When I first watched it, I only heard chenle saying it was covid siren to wear mask. They probably thought it was that. And when the staff said earthquake, you can’t even really hear the word Jeju until Kun repeated it. But take note that Kun’s voice was caught through mic which is clear to us when we watch the video but when they are sitting there, honestly you can’t confirm every single one of the guys heard it or even looked at the prompter (if there was) of the staff writing earthquake or Jeju earthquake. The coincidence of them literally just promoting their song before the siren was just unfortunate. They probably thought the staff wanted more content on their song earthquake. 🌝 anyway, no reason to spread hate. Seems like they realised what was going on after and wrote apologies just in case they hurt anyone’s feelings. But some people decided to take their apology and twist it all around, acting like if you apologised means you definitely are a bad person who did wrong? Sigh. It’s sad to live in a world like this. If you don’t like them or don’t wanna like them anymore, it’s up to you to just ignore. Don’t flood them with these comments, you’re hurting them too.

他の人が言うように本来の地震とこの曲が示すearthquake とは別物だ、という意見は理解できます。しかし、それとは別に震災の被災者からしてみれば映像や歌詞に不快感、恐怖感を覚えるのです。

author: @user-xc4lk6zs5q
text:
最初このタイトルが出た時から、少し抵抗感はありましたが、これもエンタメの一種として消化しようと努力しました。しかし、昨日の一件で嫌悪感は確信に変わりました。
韓国人の方が分かりやすいように例えると、「沈没」というタイトルで、沈没事故を連想させるようなことが起きた時に、歌って踊っているような状況です。何年経っても傷は癒えないのです。
昨日のメンバーが地震をそういう認識で行ったことも悪いし、これを制作した人たちもどうかなと思ってしまいます。
いくら私が日本人だからとは言え、地震をもろ想像させるようなメイクや音楽、舞台も良くないんじゃ無いかなと思っています。
謝罪したメンバーに対してこれ以上批判したり、ファンがメンバーに教育したり、脱退要求なんてことは求めていないので、今後日本で活動する時や日本人メンバーがいる中で、この曲に対して誠実に向き合っていってほしいと思っています。
昨日起きた地震の被害が少ないことを祈っております。

author: @user-xg4ht1zd7m
text:
I can’t support this song because of the title, the lyrics, and the sets. We Japanese suffered an enormous earthquake in 2011, and over 10,000 people passed away. We can’t forget such a huge earthquake, and Japanese members in NCT might think, too. (Some of the scenes in this track video remind me the 2011’s earthquake.) In addition, recently there are a lot of huge earthquakes in the southern Japan. We are living with the fears of happening earthquakes every day.
I know there are the culture differences, but this song will make people sad, and worried. I love NCT, and I’m such a huge fun of K-POP for a long time. I don’t wanna see a lot of people will be sad by listening to NCT’s song.
Please rethink about this song, and please think about the fans from overseas who have been suffered from earthquakes. 
Sorry about my bad English, but I just want you all to know about the fact.

.지진 경보 울렸고
애들 코로나인줄 알고 마스크 쓰라고 뭐 이런말 하다가 지진인걸 스엠 스탭들이 알려줌
김도영은 어? earthquake라고 말했고 스텝 사인을 보고 멈추고 아무말 안 함. (이때 모두가 지진임을 인지)그런데도  이마크는 노래를 불렀고 서영호는 추임새를 넣으며 춤을 춤. 앞에 스탭분들이 말리라고하자 그 신호를 눈치챈 멤버들(성찬.지성 등)이 이마크와 서영호를 말리고 일단락됨.
후에 멤버들은 사과문을 바로 올렸음.내용은 멤버가 직접 작성하지만 스토리로 올릴지 게시물로 올릴지는 회사가 결정하는 거라 멤버에게 뭐라할 수는 없음.
하지만 스토리로 올렸고 이마크 서영호는 맞춤법과 성의가 없다고 또 다시 문제가됨.
엔시티 행동 자체는 명백한 실수이고 잘못이니까 시즈니분들 선넘는 쉴드는 치지 말아요. 반성하게 두는 게 모두를 위해 좋은 거 같습니다

author: @sc9376
text: When TAEYONG first came out on this mv (& throughout), I was 😱. No matter how many times I see him, his close ups are amazing and watching him perform exciting! Then the YUTA's close up came on screen & I almost passed out!! 😍 My ultimate bias on NCT (he & Shotaro share the top of my bias list since Taro was the reason I found NCT to begin with)!! There needs to more focus on this overall talented vocal, dancing & visual King YUTA!! Finally, TAEIL (I mentioned it somewhere else for another song) beyond this man's obvious awesome vocal talent & range, every time I see him on a new mv or performance, he's crushing it, not to mention wrecking my bias list (although no one will ever be able to move YUTA/TARO out of the #1 spot!!) 😁 Those 3 stood out the most for me & many others in our group with this mv but all did great -loved seeing Johnny rap & I couldn't help but laugh when I saw Jungwoo's Hanson shirt, so cute...he's adorable 😅! 👏 I just have to say what so many in our group feel ~ all members in NCT are no doubt talented but obvious ones are too over-exposed & a lot of us are tired of seeing them 😤, then sadly there are the others who deserve more focus & aren't getting it at all!! Come on SM!! 👏👏🤩💚🎶🎤🎵😎💚

author: @ririko2022
text:
Honesty, Earthquake is my trauma. East Japan eartquake gave our to too much damages. I can't accept this song and this concept... 'cause there are flames, collapsed buildings,and so on. These scenes digging up my memory of terrible eartquake.   NCT127 is boys group of active on a global stage. They,and their managers or producers should pay attention to natural disasters. Everyone should know that there are many people that hurt in heart because of disasters.

But,when they sang the word "tornado" we didn't point out it.  I have  feeling that we should don't accuse "Earthquake"of unscrupulous in defiance of that...    

Anyways, what I want to tell you in the end is, just, I was scared to see this Earthquake's directing. I don't want watch  that their cool performance to turn into fear through producing.

text:
NCTの中でも 日本人メンバーが居て、更に日本で活動をしている127に、なぜ このタイトルの歌を歌わせるのか不思議でならない。
日本は地震大国。
地震は揺れるだけではなく、津波も誘発し、沢山の生活や命を奪います。
1度起これば、震源地から離れている地域でも余震の日々。
復旧も何年もかかります。
この恐怖や不安を 分からなくても 想像する事は SMには 誰一人 居なかったのでしょうか？
NCT127が大好きなだけに ショックは大きいです。

author: @NhiNguyen-xe5zl
text: ‘New Axis’ is the intro of the album with powerful raps and a heavy bassline. The title track ‘Universe (Let’s Play Ball)' is a hip-hop dance song and the rap part is written by Mark. ‘Earthquake’ is a hip hop dance song; ‘OK!’ is an R&B song with hip hop sounds; ‘Birthday Party’ is a groovy dance song; ‘Know Now’ is an R&B pop song while ‘Dreaming’ is a house song with R&B elements. ‘Round&Round’, Miracle’, ‘Vroom’ and ‘Sweet Dream’ are medium tempo R&B pop songs. ‘Good Night’ is a ballad with some of the main vocalists of NCT. Finally, the second title track, the pop ballad ‘Beautiful’, will be performed by all 21 members and has been written by Johnny, Taeyong, Mark, Hendery and Jeno.

author: @mimimada734

author: @NhiNguyen-xe5zl
text:
1. ‘New Axis’ - Taeyong, Mark, Yangyang
2. ‘Universe (Let’s Play Ball)’ - TITLE TRACK. Doyoung, Jungwoo, Mark, Xiaojun, Jeno, Haechan, Jaemin, Yangyang, Shotaro
3. ‘Earthquake’ - The fixed sub-unit NCT 127
4. ‘OK!’ - Taeyong, Yuta, Ten, Mark, Hendery, Jeno, Yangyang
5. ‘Birthday Party’ - Johnny, Yuta, Jungwoo, Hendery, Jaemin, Shotaro, Chenle, Jisung
6. ‘Know Now’ - Johnny, Doyoung, Mark, Renjun, Jeno, Jaemin, Yangyang, Sungchan
7. ‘Dreaming’ - The fixed sub-unit NCT Dream
8. ‘Round&Round’ - Taeil, Ten, Jaehyun, Xiaojun, Haechan, Sungchan
9. ‘Miracle’ - The fixed Chinese sub-unit WayV
10. ‘Vroom’ - Kun, Jaehyun, Jungwoo, Hendery, Shotaro, Chenle, Jisung
11. ‘Sweet Dream’ - Taeil, Kun, Jaehyun, Haechan, Chenle
12. ‘Good Night’ - Taeil, Doyoung, Xiaojun, Renjun
13. ‘Beautiful’ - TITLE TRACK. All 21 NCT members

author: @ayshaubaid7434
text:
[Intro: Mark, Johnny]
Yeah, what a big earthquake
Make it crack wherever we want
Every time all around the world

[Verse 1: Taeyong, Mark, Jungwoo, Jaehyun, *Yuta*]
My heart has struck the earth
A time in which something is about to change
Can't stop, won't stop
As if I was smashed onto the ground
Even if lightning strikes the earth
Don't mind to you, come through
We are stopped in the same place
You and I are so boring
I don't want to stay still, I want to go
To another place where the expanded NEO ZONE is materialized
*A sign you know is about to start*

[Pre-Chorus: Doyoung, Haechan]
Don't let go
If you avoid change, you'll еasily get stuck, baby
Yeah, that's the only rеason that makes me move

[Chorus: All, Taeil, Doyoung]
This earthquake that has just begun (Shake it)
The changing domino that destroyed my toes
Turning it upside down and creating it again
A world is completed with the rotation of dreams
Don't let me down
We are out of control
The map we're leaving behind, burn it up
When we shake, earthquake
When we shake, earthquake
Destroy yesterday and the past won't be here

[Bridge: Jungwoo, Haechan, Taeil, Doyoung, *Johnny*]
Thunder above the cherry blossoms
Another rule that collides and collapses
I want more change, don't stay the same, no
In the crack between time
Starting again are you and I
My dreamed world I created, oh
*My eyes open up again
I step towards the next level, oh yeah
What we made is a world that has grown bigger than infinity*

[Chorus: All, Yuta, Haechan, Taeil]
This earthquake that has just begun (Shake it)
The changing domino that destroyed my toes
What we created is a world that has grown bigger than infinity
Don't let me down
Move on, we lost control
Everything we're leaving behind, burn it up
When we shake, earthquake
When we shake, earthquake
The earthquake that surpassed the limits and changed us

[Outro: Jaehyun]
When we shake, when we shake
When we shake, earthquake

author: @AT-pb4wr
text:
自分が投稿したコメントに返信したのに反映されなくなっているようなので再投稿。

地震だけでなく災害は世界中で発生しています。日本だけに特別な配慮を望んでいるわけではありません。
震災を体験した人、被災地から離れた場所に住んでいた人も当時を思いだし複雑な感情を持つ人も多い。そんな人達に「ハリケーンや火山はどうなる」と言って何になるの？
2018年に悠太の故郷大阪で大きな地震起きてその時彼は日本公式から被災者を気遣うメッセージを出しました。
悠太が産まれた1995年にも大きな地震が発生家族も被災者です。その頃悠太はお腹の中にいた頃でしょう。ご家族が無事で本当に良かった。

author: @橙-p6b
text:
曲のタイトルである地震の意味やMVで表現された世界観が思った以上に直接的で、嫌な気持ちになってしまって、大好きなnct127のパフォーマンスを純粋に楽しむことができませんでした。

個人的に日本人の私には、地震をプラスの意味で捉えることは理解し難く受け入れ難いです。

また地震を比喩として用いずとも、"過去を忘れて新しいスタートを切って大きな変化を起こす"というコンセプトや曲調は、別のフレーズでも表現できたのではないでしょうか？

少なくとも日本デビューをして、ターゲット層の中に日本の市場が入っているイリチルにこの曲を歌わせるべきではなかったと思います。

純粋にこの曲を楽しんでいる方々を否定するつもりは全くありません。ただ、私は今回のアルバムについては買うのを控えます。

author: @hshs3908
text:
不快の一言に尽きる。そもそもグローバルグループという名目で、日本が活動拠点に入っている事に加えて日本人が在籍しているのに、何故このタイトルなんだろうか。日本が地震大国だということを、事務所は認識出来ていないのか？大地震になると、天井が崩れ、道路は断裂し、簡単に火の海になってしまうというのに？人が数え切れないほど理不尽に亡くなってしまうというのに？
イリチルは有り得ない様な多忙のスケジュールでこの曲を準備してきたのだと思っている。イリチルはきっと悪く無いが、事務所の配慮が余りにも足りなさ過ぎる。
普段イリチルが大好きなシズニだが、擁護のしようが全く無い。

SM, I am so sorry. I feel angry. What's so cool about earthquakes? I guess the intention of this music video is to say, "We're cool because we have so much power that we can shake the earth!" To SM, not to the members. From a Japanese fan.

이해찬 이마크가 올해 한 일

드림 첫 정규컴백 - 맛 (오랜만에 7드림에 6년만에 드림 첫 정규)

둘다 드림이랑 127활동에 U까지 함

5월 정규컴백 - 6월 리패키지 - 9월 정규컴백 - 10월 리패키지 - 12월 컴백, 마마, 127콘서트

author: @angelmaymendoza8703
text:
Why you'd want to listen more than once: because it's a complex track.
On first my listen, Taeil, Yuta, and Doyoung's vocals are on point. Mark's parts, too - his voice and rap style suits the track so well. Best of all, Johnny's lines are THERE and are point. These stood out the most.
The track is all over the place (in the way that it has lots of layers) that I'd have to listen again - there were a lot of melodies and harmonizing behind the track and lead vocals probably that I wasn't able to appreciate every detail and every member on first listen.


And also, I was distracted by the visuals and the choreo. As per usual. HAHA here ends my first reaction review, now I'm off to listen to it again~

text: Enserio me encanta me encanta me encanta!, NCT es a lo que le rezamos cada día. Los amo demasiado gracias por ser tan increíblemente talentosos y darnos arte, estoy demasiado emocionada con que ya salga el álbum, mis ojos lloran por el brillo de 9 hermosos diamantes. ㅠㅠㅠㅠㅠㅠㅠㅠㅠ

En menos de 4 meses trabajaron tan duro y nos entregaron lo mejor de ellos.
Orgullosa de stanear a estos dioses.
Aguante nct 127 loco.
Los amo muchísimo ♡

Of course, NCT 127's songs if examined by experts, such as producers, vocalists, sound engineers etc, even videographers too from various countries, all of them state that their songs are experimental but the compositions, although unique, are still good, with 127's capable vocals make their songs musically quality from various sides. That's why I'm proud of 127, they can bear blasphemy about their music genre that different from the usual music. But it turns out that the experts who listend their song are very good songs, and finally became a legend in the world. They're trully  trendsetters. So please don't judge if just not to your taste in music. Because their songs have been recognized for their quality by experts.

author: @myraclesname
text:
I'm so sorry to ruin the mood, but here's my criticism because it barely exists in this community. 
NCT has lost its flavor. 
I'm not saying that's a bad thing, but I'm not saying it's a good thing either. i enjoyed every subunits recent comeback but I've noticed how their distinctive sound has changed. Especially when it comes to 127. It hurts to say this, but they when will they release something exciting, something that we're used to yet not at all used to? I notice how I'm slowly falling out of being fan, maybe I've just lost my interest overall, but this song is a let down as well as the other subunit's track videos. Not music-wise, but nct and SM-wise. The styling is boring, the dances are so not nct (if that makes sense) and the sound is just... Generic. It's too "kpop" almost. I don't know how to explain it lol. But yeah I guess it's just my opinion. Accepting the fact that I might just not want to stan NCT anymore is harder than expected.

author: @rebeckaroy6790
text:
Yes siree, I had high expectations with a song title like Earthquake....  and 127 delivers :D  Really cool use of the drones... why are they being tracked?.....
I love how Mark uses his voice so playfully and later slides into some lovely vocals (and way to kill that choreo my son!)
TY is killing it in that sleeveless jumper and his approach to choreo and rap flow are soooo riveting
Love seeing Johnny getting the lines and centre these days, he feels like such an anchor to me
Yuta's vocal agility is getting even better, he cuts right through
Doyoung sounds divine as always and that is a good look for him, ,how is he always so elegant yet powerful?
Jungwoo makes the Hanson tshirt and cardigan look really work and his lines were soooo great
Haechan is just such a killer whenever he is on screen or in your ears, he knows how to make the most of every moment
Jaehyun was really bringing the drama in his scenes and I love to see those new angles
Yes, thank you, plenty of Taeil focus time in just this little track vid, keep it up editors!
